name: Wasp Network
description: The story of five Cuban political prisoners who had been imprisoned by the United States since the late 1990s on charges of espionage and murder.

review.author: Sir_AmirSyarif
review.heading: Quite a mess
review.reviewBody: Olivier Assayas' 'Wasp Network' had the opportunity for substantial dramatic material with its fascinating based-on-a-true-story plot and a star-studded cast. Unfortunately, the story is so jam-packed with various narratives and characters it becomes convoluted, confusing, and tiring to watch. Quite a mess.

keywords: spy,cuba,based on true story,written by director,communism
